-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-29/zarechnaya-coal-sets-10-8-coupon-on-3-billion-rubles-of-bonds.html
Zarechnaya Coal Co. , a Russian
miner, set a coupon of 10.8 percent on 3 billion rubles ($93
million) of bonds with a three-year  put option .  Zarechnaya Coal, based in Siberia, announced the terms in
regulatory filings today. The producer is controlled by
businessman Viktor Nusenkis, owner of the Ukrainian steelmaker
Donetskstal Group, according to Forbes magazine.  The company increased coal output 12 percent in the first
11 months of the year to 8.4 million metric tons, its website
shows. Zarechnaya was  Russia â€™s fifth-largest producer of coal
for power plants in the first half, according to Dnipropetrovsk-
based Metal Expert.  To contact the reporters on this story:
